{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Resets "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" to its uncancelled state.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO19CancellableProtocolPAAE5resetyyF","title":"reset()","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reset","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"symbolKind":"method"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol\/reset()"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol\/reset()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"reset","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If cancellable is currently in use by any cancellable operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then the behavior of this function is undefined.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that it is generally not a good idea to reuse an existing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cancellable for more operations after it has been cancelled once,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as this function might tempt you to do. The recommended practice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is to drop the reference to a cancellable after cancelling it,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and let it die with the outstanding async operations. You should","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"create a fresh cancellable for further async operations."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the event that a [signal[Cancellable](\/\/documentation\/gio\/cancellable\/oncancelled(flags:handler:)] signal handler is currently"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running, this call will block until the handler has finished."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Calling this function from a signal handler will therefore result in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"deadlock.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol/reset()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Resets "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to its uncancelled state."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol\/reset()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol\/reset()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"reset"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"title":"reset()"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GCancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}